cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DL

This paper proposes a system for automatically detecting and extracting new technology terms related to Artificial Intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to identify relevant terms in text, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on AI technologies, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a probable sub-category. The paper also mentions semantic labels and AI domains, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.DL (Machine Learning and Pattern Recognition).
